data.title: Central Square Foundation
data.meta_description: The team behind CSF working towards improving school education in India.
data.text:
Abhimanyu works as a Senior Project Lead in the EdTech team and is based out of Delhi. He currently focuses on improving and scaling various edtech products catering to the FLN segment to ensure continued learning at home. Prior to CSF, he worked with 321 Education Foundation after completing the Teach For India (TFI) Fellowship in 2017. At 321, he collaborated with more than 30 low-cost private schools across Mumbai and Bangalore to improve classroom instructional practices and student mastery in grades K-3. As a TFI Fellow, Abhimanyu taught 37 students in grades 2 and 3 in Ahmedabad. He holds an MBA in Strategy from Rotterdam School of Management, Erasmus University and an undergraduate degree in engineering from NMIMS, Mumbai. In his free time, he enjoys watching Formula 1, exploring the best food joints in town and travelling to new destinations.

Abhishek works as a Project Lead in the District Project Management Unit (UP) team and is based out of Delhi. Prior to CSF, he managed and led multiple CBSE projects including CTET, working in the Government Project team. Abhishek has also worked with Teach For India (TFI) and 321 Education Foundation. At 321, he worked as a Kaizen Manager on the monitoring aspects of the school strengthening/teacher training programs. During his time as a TFI fellow, he taught Maths to 210 students in a government school and iTeach school across 2 years. Abhishek is a commerce graduate from National PG College, Lucknow University. During his free time, he can be found solving puzzles, number problems, and travelling.

Aditi works on Early Childhood Education at CSF. Her work focuses on two areas: state projects and salience building. In her previous role at CSF, she was with the Private Schools (Governance) team wherein she worked on assessments for grades 3, 5, and 8. She joined CSF in 2019 after completing her Masters in International Education Policy from Harvard University. Previously, she worked with Teach For India in Hyderabad as a Teaching Fellow and Program Manager. Deep curiosity to understand systems better and work with complex problems motivated her to move away from an engineering background. She enjoys reading, watching TV shows, cooking new recipes, and planning her next trip back home!

Akashi Kaul is currently leading the RMEAL Team at CSF and is based out of Delhi. She holds a Bachelors Degree in Literature from Punjab University, a Masters Degree in Communication from SIMC, a Masters in Education Degree from University of Pennsylvania, and a PhD in Education Policy from George Mason University. She specializes in evaluation methods and designs, with close to 15 years of experience. Her previous roles include leading the education, child protection and equity vertical at a leading Indian RMEL firm, contributing to external evaluations for NIH, NSF, NASA and US Dept. of Labour and State as an evaluation expert and conducting independent research on advancing evaluation methodologies in the global south. She enjoys designing research and evaluation for complex interventions in complex contexts, particularly with an eye towards using innovative methodologies and learning mechanisms.

Akshay works with the Human Resources team at CSF as a Manager and is based out of Delhi. Prior to CSF, Akshay has worked extensively with The /Nudge Institute, where he spearheaded collaborative initiatives at The/Nudge Forums inaugural Charcha. This endeavor brought together brilliant minds from diverse sectorslivelihoods, tech, policy, and businessin a collective pursuit of driving meaningful change. His involvement in talent acquisition at The/Nudge Institute is his most cherished memory. He not only identified exceptional talent but also got to cultivate an environment that values diverse perspectives and contributions. In his free time, Akshay likes to read rare reads from Wikipedia and to do heritage walks around the city appreciating and exploring different art forms.

Akshay works in the State Reform team, supporting the Haryana state in the implementation of the NIPUN Bharat Mission. Currently, his key responsibilities include monitoring, capacity building and operational support for the NIPUN Haryana Mission. Previously, he worked as an IB analyst in the Consumer & Retail sector at Bank of America. Akshay holds a postgraduate diploma in management from IIM Kozhikode and a bachelors in business studies from Delhi University. In his free time, he can be found making impromptu trips to Himachal or thinking about making impromptu trips to Himachal.

Akshit works with CSFs SRT Team and supports the implementation of its FLN program across 3 states in North and Central India.He holds a B.Tech Degree from Punjab Engineering College, Chandigarh and loves to quiz. Prior to CSF, Akshit has worked as a Research Analyst with Mckinseys Digital vertical and briefly for the governance consulting firm Samagra; where he supported Uttar Pradesh governments healthcare service delivery program, Mission Niramaya.He enjoys sketching and is always up for a conversation about rock bands and Formula 1.

Alankita works as a Project Lead in the RMEAL team at CSF and is based in Delhi. She holds a M.Phil. (Political Science) from the University of Delhi and is currently pursuing her Ph.D. Prior to joining CSF, she has explored both university lectureship and research. Alankita worked with the National Assessment Centre-PARAKH at NCERT where she was a part of the team responsible for the development and administration of National-level large-scale assessments like the Foundational Learning Study (FLS), 2022 and National Achievement Survey (NAS), 2021. In her free time, Alankita can be found reading fiction and chilling at beaches.

Amola works as a Project Manager in the EdTech Team and is based out of Delhi. She works to improve and scale diverse EdTech solutions. She works closely with grantee organizations and funders to develop a supply of vibrant products for children from low-income backgrounds. She joined CSF after graduating from Ashoka University with a bachelors degree in Political Science. She is interested in the intersection of technology and development, and opportunities to see change up close. Her time outside of work is spent chasing her cat, bouldering, and traveling.

Ananth works with the state reform team as a Project Lead and is based out of Panchkula. Ananth holds an engineering degree from NIT Trichy and a management degree from IIM Calcutta. Prior to CSF, he has worked on pivotal roles at GDi Partners, BCG, IPAC, and Saint-Gobain. He seamlessly blends corporate expertise with his lifelong passion for education, characterized by an insatiable curiosity for positive change. When free, Youll find him engrossed in books or engaged in interesting debates with anyone who wishes to join in.

Ananya works as a Project Manager in the Early Childhood Education team and is based out of Lucknow. Prior to CSF, she was a Teach for India fellow (2022) in low-income government schools in Delhi, she is now committed to eliminating education inequity through systemic reforms informed by grassroot insights. She was also a Young India Fellow and holds a degree in Psychology from Lady Shri Ram College. Ananya can often be found sketching on prohibited surfaces, volunteering at animal shelters, or chatting with the local strays.

Ananya works with the State Reform team as a Project Manager and is based out of Panchkula. Ananya has completed her bachelors degree from St. Stephens College, University of Delhi. Prior to CSF, Ananya has worked with Ernst & Young for (close to) four and a half years and supported different government and public sector clients on Investment Promotion initiatives. She has experience in product development and digital transformation. She is into drama, acting, and dance.

Aniket works as Project Manager in the RMEAL team and is based out of Delhi. He has a strong commitment to evidence-based policy making in India. He holds a masters degree in Public Policy from Jindal School of Government and Public Policy, Delhi, and a bachelors degree in Computer Engineering from Maharashtra Institute of Technology, Pune. With prior experience at Samobdhi Research and Communications and the Ministry of Home Affairs, Aniket brings invaluable insights to his role. In his leisure time, he enjoys immersing himself in video games and exploring history through documentaries.

Anindita works in the Administration Team at CSF as Manager-Facilities and Resources and is based out of Delhi. She holds a Bachelors degree in Economics (Hons) from Jesus and Mary College, DU. Prior to CSF, she has worked with various Indian and multinational companies like the Spice Group, Sangeet Natak Akademi, ChrysCapital, American Express and Global Innovation & Technology Alliance (CII) all of which have helped widen her knowledge base. She enjoys interacting with people from all spheres of work and also being socially active. She is an avid traveller and passionate about art, music and dance.

Anirudh works as a Senior Project Lead in the RMEAL team and is based in Delhi. He holds a Masters degree in Education (Research Design and Methodologies) from University of Oxford and a Masters degree in Education (Elementary) from Tata Institute of Social Science, Mumbai. Prior to CSF, he has over a decade of experience across more than ten countries working with global think tanks, research institutions, and government stakeholders to produce high-quality, evidence-based research outputs.

Anirudh works as a Project Manager in the EdTech team and is based out of Delhi. Prior to joining CSF, he worked as a business manager at Internshala wherein he was working to bridge the gap between millions of employers and jobseekers in the country. He holds a masters degree in development studies from the Tata Institute of Social Sciences and a bachelors degree in computer science and engineering from Amrita University. In his free time, he enjoys playing football, exploring new places, and catching-up with the latest happenings in the world of politics.

Ankit works as a Senior Project Lead in the District Project Management Unit (UP) team and is based out of Delhi. Prior to joining CSF, he was working as a management consultant and was involved in planning and implementation of upcoming MDB funded metro/rail projects in Delhi NCR region. He has extensive experience of supporting government clients with solutions based on project portfolio management, financial analysis & planning and performance improvement. Ankit holds a bachelors degree in Civil Engineering from IIT-Roorkee and MBA in Business Management from XLRI-Jamshedpur. He believes that Indias journey from a developing country to a developed country can be expedited by reforming the school education landscape in the country. He is passionate about travelling in mountains.

Ankur is committed to solving Indias development problems like quality education in the public system. In 10+ years of experience, he has designed and implemented scalable models that delivered. He started his career as an entrepreneur and provided Ed-tech services to 31 low-income private schools in rural Haryana, supporting the career progression of 3600+ students to top-notch colleges in the country. In 2015, he got his first multi-state engagement with Ravi J. Matthai Centre for Educational Innovation, IIM Ahmedabad, where his team could impact government school students from over 16,000+ schools of Gujarat via GCERT. Later, working as an ED of a non-profit, he spearheaded a state-wide educational transformation project with the Haryana government, impacting over 4900+ teachers and 2.6 lacs+ students during COVID. In 2021, he worked with Delhi Government to set up the Desh Ke Mentors program, Indias largest mentoring program supporting over nine lakh school students in exploring their career journeys. This short stint with Delhi Government helped him bring transformation from within the system. Currently, as a part of the Government Projects team at CSF, he is leading TicTacLearn  Indias largest content repository of Maths & Science educational content available in six languages. Ankur earned a post-graduate diploma in management from XLRI Jamshedpur and a bachelors degree in computer science & engineering from Guru Jambeshwar University, Hisar.

Anuj works as a Project Manager in the Classroom Instruction and Practice team and is based out of Delhi. He was associated with Teach for India as a fellow in Delhi, where he taught grade 4 & 5 students at a budget-private school near Bhajanpura, Seelampur. During his fellowship, he realised the power of an effective curriculum on a larger landscape of the education system and, hence, explored different roles around curriculum and international pedagogy. Prior to joining CSF, he worked as a Teaching Faculty with Shiv Nadar School. He is often described as a go to person by his friends and you may find him binge-watching sitcoms during his spare time.

Anurag works with the State reform team as Project Manager and is based out of Bhopal. He holds an integrated Bachelors and Masters Degree in Civil Engineering from Indian Institute of Technology, Madras. Before joining CSF, he was working as an associate consultant with Ernst and Young LLP in planning and implementation of the public transportation projects. He wants to be part of Indias transformational journey and solve complex grass root problems of

Indian society. He enjoys reading non-fiction books, playing online blitz chess and loves watching biopic movies.

Anustup leads the Classroom Instruction & Practices (CIP) team at CSF. In his role, he works with multiple CSF partner organizations and state government agencies to support the implementation of the FLN mission. Prior to working at CSF, his work involved supporting and scaling up an entrepreneurial venture named XSEED Education. Anustup joined CSF to pursue his passion to improve public education at scale. He did his masters in education at the Harvard Graduate School of Education and Public Policy at Georgia Tech. He is passionate about equipping teachers with the right tools and skills to succeed in the classroom. In his free time, he enjoys listening to podcasts and is constantly on the search for the next viral meme.

Arabinda works with the Strategic Support States team as a Project Lead and is based out at Bhubaneswar. Arabinda holds a Ph.D. in Economics from Gokhale Institute of Politics and

Economics, Pune and Master in Population Studies from IIPS, Mumbai, and has worked with diverse teams across India.Prior to joining CSF, Arabinda has worked with UNICEF, CARE,

UNFPA, INDEPTH Network and KHPT, Bangalore. He is a development sector professional whose primary engagement in development sector as monitoring, evaluation and research domain. He has designed and implemented various research project in developmental issues including education for over 16 years with a deep interest and commitment towards bridging practice with scientific research findings.

Arpit works with the State Reform Team at CSF as a Project Lead and is based out of Panchkula. Arpit holds a Masters in Business Management from IIM Lucknow complementing his professional expertise with a robust academic foundation. Previously a Teach For India fellow in 2016, he brings a wealth of experience in the education sector, particularly in the management of expansive projects. In his free time, Arpit enjoys exploring unconventional destinations, demonstrating a keen interest in offbeat travel experiences during his leisure time

Atma works as a Project Lead in the EdTech team and is based out of Delhi. She is responsible for managing stakeholders including researchers, grantee organizations, and implementation partners to execute projects that can drive the evidence generation agenda for EdTech. Prior to joining CSF, Atma was part of the Corporate Services Division at the United Nations Environment Programme (UNEP) in Geneva providing partnerships and stakeholder engagement support to governments in Somalia, Ghana, Uganda, Mozambique, Iraq, Colombia, and South Asia. She has also previously worked with multiple organisations within the development sector such as UNDP India, UNJIU Geneva, and the SOS Childrens Village in Nepal. Her interest in the education sector comes from her time as a Teach For India (2016) Fellow, serving as a full-time teacher in a low-income government school in Yerwada, Pune. Atma holds a bachelors degree in Social Sciences from TISS and a masters degree in Development Studies from the Graduate Institute of Geneva. Outside of work, Atma is always trying to read at least 3 books simultaneously and hopes to write her own someday.

Avnish Kumar works with the State FLN Projects team as a District Consultant based in Bihar. He brings years of experience in child rights, education, and governance with masters in accounts. He found his purpose when he witnessed how soft skills enabled him and his peers. Previously he has been a Fellow at Transforming Rural India Foundation under Aspirational District Transformation Program and Gandhi Fellow for two years. He has worked closely with the District Magistrate and supported the district administration in strategic planning, project management, implementation, and fundraising across rural India. He loves writing poems and stories. He aspires to drive change in society at scale

Ayush Prabhat works as a Project Manager in the District Project Management Unit (UP) team and is based out of Agra. He graduated with a Bachelors in Humanities and Social Sciences from University of Delhi. Prior to CSF, he worked at Teach for India where he had the opportunity to work on various projects. Apart from being passionate about the possibilities in our classrooms, Ayush is always up for long walks. He enjoys exploring curious questions about the world we share together.

Ayush works with the State Reform Team at CSF as a Project Associate, and is based out of Bhopal. He graduated from Shri Ram College of Commerce (SRCC), University of Delhi with a degree in B.Com (H). Prior to joining CSF, he worked in the Founders Office at an Early Stage E-Commerce Startup. He has gained experience as a Management Consultant with Zinnov and as a Founder of a social innovation think-tank. He has also worked in the slums of Delhi, leading a venture to supply affordable Sanitary Napkins to all females. In his free time, you will find him reading, trekking, running marathons, and enjoying open water swimming.

Barasha works with the State FLN Projects team as a Project Consultant and is based out of Guwahati. She holds a bachelors graduation in Political Science (Honours) from Ramjas College and a Masters in Political Science from Indraprastha College for Women. She was a Teach For India Fellow (2018 cohort, Delhi) and has worked as a Program Manager in NEAID implementing various education projects across Northeast India. Barasha finds painting therapeutic and loves to travel around observing different cultures and traditions of diverse communities, while enjoying the nature. Also, she is an adventure junkie and a thrill seeker.

Bhagyashree works as a Research Associate with the Classroom Instruction and Practice team at Central Square Foundation. Prior to joining CSF, Bhagyashree worked with Samavesh on primary education for 3 years in Dewas, Madhya Pradesh, where closely worked with 112 teachers on foundational numeracy and literacy, as well as early childhood education. She liaised with various stakeholders such as block officials, students, SMC, and the tribal community. In TPD, she developed the modules for teacher training programs. During her time as a volunteer, Bhagyashree taught social studies to till 5th std in Bhandara, Maharashtra. She has completed a Masters in Education (MA Education) from Azim Premji University, Bengaluru and Commerce graduate from Nagpur University. During her free time, Bhagyashree enjoys writing poetry.

Bhawna works a Project Manager in the Finance Team and is based oout of Delhi. She is responsible for day-to-day accounting and managing the monthly MIS, along with employee engagement. Bhawna has spent 5+ years in the corporate sector as a Finance Executive and has experience of all compliance handling like including GST, ESI, PF, etc. Bhawna holds an M.COM degree From Indira Gandhi National Open University along with a Bachelors degree in Commerce from Delhi University. During her free time, she enjoys watching movies and TV series, listening to music and travelling with family and friends.

Chandni Kalra works with the State FLN Projects team as Project Consultant based in Bhubaneswar. She has Experience in combining human and material resources to deliver excellent education, ensuring fair treatment with equal opportunity when it comes to access to resources. She started off her journey in the Education space as a TFI Fellow, moved on to be a member of the Selection team at TFI and then joined LEAD to understand stakeholder management better. Having explored all these she is here at CSF to learn and grow with everything that this role has to offer. You can often find her lost in her Lalaland, far away from the chaos with a bowl of Mississippi.

Chetan joins the State Reform Team as a Project Manager and will be based out of Lucknow. He holds a B.Tech Degree in Mechanical Engineering from Alicante University, Spain. Prior to joining CSF, he worked with Teach for India, that opened his eyes to educations potential in uplifting marginalized communities. At Masai School, a high-growth startup, he led and scaled processes, witnessing the incredible talent of underserved students. In his free time, Chetan enjoys watching real-life movies and playing football, table tennis, and swimming. His journey is dedicated to empowering through education and finding inspiration in everyday triumphs.

Debatri works with the Classroom Instruction and Practice team that works closely with multiple states and partner organisations on developing and implementing the FLN Mission. Prior to CSF, Debatri has been a Program Manager at Teach for India, working with close to 40 Fellows over 3 years, building the program in first year intervention schools. She also did the TFI Fellowship, teaching Literacy and Social Studies to Primary School students in a municipal school. Debatri completed her Masters in Literature from Delhi University. During her free time, Debatri reads books and doodles with the intent to upload them on her instagram page someday.

Debesh has a diverse experience of over 15 years as a Media & Comms professional, working across the media, digital comms, and behavioural campaigns spaces. In his last professional stint, he worked with WaterAid India as the media and comms lead, where he was leading on the communications strategy and overseeing execution plans for building advocacy and thought-leadership around water, sanitation, and hygiene issues. Before that, at Youth Ki Awaaz- a youth centric online platform- he was working on developing strategy and planning online and offline campaigns on various social justice issues; business development; including building capacity for campaign acquisition and outreach for new campaigns with brands and non-profit entities. Prior to this, he has been associated with organizations like British Council; The Indian Express, The Pioneer; with brief stints at The Guardian & BBC World News, where he was working on different aspects involving: planning and executing digital comms. strategies; designing social media campaigns; digital project planning; securing and managing non-paid partnerships in areas of digital innovation; writing and reporting on features and urban lifestyle trends.

Deergha works as a Project Manager in the State Reform Team and is based out of Delhi. She graduated from the National Institute of Design, Ahmedabad. Her interest lies in exploring all the nuances of the education system. She is a designer turned educator with experience managing projects, research, and design with stakeholders from SCERT Sikkim, Azim Premji Foundation, government school teachers, and school communities in Uttarakhand, Sikkim, and Delhi. Before working with CSF, she was a fellow at Teach For India, Delhi. Deergha is never without an audiobook and has experimented extensively to concoct her version of the perfect cup of ginger chai.

Devam works as a Project Manager in the District Project Management Unit (UP) team and is based out of Jhansi. He holds a Masters in Rural Management from IRMA. Prior to CSF, he worked as an Assistant Manager at Mahindra and Mahindras. His journey reflects a keen enthusiasm for nation-building, rooted in the belief that education is key to social progress. Outside of work, Devam enjoys solo traveling, mountaineering, and playing outdoor sports, finding joy in adventure and exploration.

Devanshi works as a Project Manager in the EdTech team and is based out of Delhi. She holds a degree in Chartered Accountancy. Prior to CSF, Devanshi worked with Mahindra & Mahindra Financial Services Ltd. and Bain & Co. She ventured into the development space via a short policy making course. Her belief in education being a fundamental game changer coupled with the curiosity to understand how scale projects work brings her to CSF. In her free time, she can be seen reading, trying new yoga poses, exploring the art scene around and is always up to create an itinerary for random, scenic places.

Dinesh works with the Administration team as the Facilities Manager and is based out of Delhi. He holds a bachelors degree from University of Delhi and a Diploma in Hotel Management from the Indian Hotel Management Institute in Delhi. Prior to CSF, he was associated with firms such as Accenture, Omicron, Rockwell Automation, etc. that operate in the fields of IT and industrial automation. Most recently he worked with The Convergence Foundation for more than a year and a half. In his spare time, Dinesh enjoys traveling, listening to music and reading.

Parthajeet leads the State FLN Projects team which provides strategic support to states in their programmes to improve foundational learning. The team takes a systems approach and strengthens the academic as well as governance intiatives of the states. Parthajeet holds a PhD and Masters in Management and has more than a decade of rich national and international experience across top management consulting firms of advising governments, multi-lateral donors and foundations. In his free time, he loves to travel, read, write and listen to music.

Dr. Vaibhav Sindhi works as a Project Manager in the Classroom Instruction and Practice team and is based in one of our districts. He did his Post Graduation in Public Policy, Design & Management at the Indian School of Public Policy, Delhi. Prior to CSF, he worked at Health Department (NHM), led a team to develop COVID-19 facilities and managed critical healthcare logistics and Lifeline Foundation where he trained over 8,000 people in life-saving courses & secured funding for road safety education. His commitment to environment is showcased through his work on zero plastic policies & carbon-neutral event planning with Grant Thornton Bharat LLP. His entrepreneurial spirit is evident from his co-founding of Estudy Partner, aiding students in overseas dental education.

Eesha works as a Program Manager in the Partnerships and Strategic Initiatives team and is based out of Delhi. She holds a Bachelors degree in Computer Science and Engineering from NIT Hamirpur and a Masters degree in Development Studies from University of Sussex. Prior to CSF, she worked as a software developer in Oracle Financial Services Software (OFSS) and later as a team lead in a tech-media startup, Fossbytes. After deciding to pursue her passion for the development sector, she worked with Centre for Science of Student Learning (CSSL) where she discovered her love for education and development. In her recent engagement as a Change-Maker in Education (CMIE) Fellow with the Delhi Government. Having grown up in a military family, Eesha has traveled extensively, which has nurtured her love for exploring new places, people and cultures.

Saquib works in the District Project Management Unit (UP) team as a District Consultant and is based out of Aligarh. He holds a Bachelors of Science in Physics from Aligarh Muslim University (AMU), Uttar Pradesh and a Masters in Social Work from Maulana Azad National Urdu University (MANUU), Hyderabad, Telangana. Prior to CSF, Saquib has been a Gandhi fellow and has worked with organisations like Avanti Fellows, Aashiyana Foundation and GDI Partners. He has worked on programme implementation, baseline, end line, sessions, training of children and staff of the child care institutions. He also conducted baseline assessment training for more than 150+ block resource persons (BRPs/ABRCs) for proper execution of assessment and test conduction in school. Saquib likes to swim, play cricket and carom and has also started stock trading as a hobby.

Garima works as a Project Lead with the Strategic Support States Team and is based out of Delhi. She supports implementation of foundational literacy and numeracy programs to improve learning levels across five states. Previously, she worked with D. E. Shaw Research, out of their Hyderabad office, leading projects in operations and recruitment for the computational drug discovery research firm. Garima has an undergraduate degree in Commerce and Economics from Indraprastha College for Women, University of Delhi. When not working, she spends time traveling, reading, and practicing yoga.

Gaurav works as a Senior Project Lead in the District Project Management Unit (UP) team and is based out of Delhi. His journey with the education sector started as a fellow in Teach for India where he taught a classroom of 50 girls in 5th and 6th grade. Post fellowship, he worked as a Program Manager in TFIs Delhi team, building professional and personal capacity in 30 fellows. Prior to CSF, Gaurav co-founded his own non-profit, Slam Out Loud, and led it as the Chief Operating Officer for 5 years. Gaurav has a Masters in Public Administration from National University of Singapore and is a certified action learning coach from the Action Learning Center, UK. Post work, he spends time solving puzzles, hoarding trivia, discovering new poetry, reading non-fiction and having conversations over/about food.

Gaurav Saroha works as a Project Manager in the School Governance team and is based out of Guwahati. He has previously worked with the Quality Council of India as an Associate Manager; worked on projects likeMade in India Brand Scheme and Indias Trade Deficit Policy. His work centred around government advisory, policy making and implementation. He has completed Young India Fellowship from Ashoka University and graduated with a BTech in Computer Science and Engineering. Most of his free time goes dabbling into foreign language movies and reading non-fiction books.

Gayathri joins CSF as a Project Manager in the Strategic Support States Team, Telangana and is based at Medchal-Malkajgiri. She holds a Bachelors Degree in Physics & Electronics from Loyola Academy  Alwal, Secunderaba. Prior to CSF, she has worked as a full-time Teaching Fellow & as a Transformational Teaching Fellow with Teach for India, Hyderabad. As the Content Advisor at TFI, Hyderabad, she held communities of practice for Secondary Science teachers in content and pedagogy. She established the first community centre in Teach for India, Hyderabad, impacting students, alumni and stakeholders of the community and designed a Science curriculum for the high school students of Council on International Educational Exchange (CIEE)  USA, a global community. In her free time, Gayathri can be found exploring street food or discussing Marvel comics.

Geetika works in the RMEAL team as a Senior Project Lead, designing and implementing assessments for different stakeholders in the school education system. She has been working in the education sector for more than a decade now. In her previous instinct as well, she has worked for designing and implementing large-scale assessments for different geographies to understand the impact of various programs. She has worked with teachers for their professional development and with policy makers to implement educational initiatives across geographies. Geetika is an IIM Lucknow alumnus, PhD in Economics, trained in business and data analytics and masters in business administration. At heart she is a teacher and always tries to make things simpler for people to understand and implement. She likes to blend creativity and simplicity in the teaching, training by weaving story around work. She hails from the royal blue city of Jodhpur, married to a finance professional- professor and both love cooking and exploring food. In her free time, she can be seen playing mathematical games and doing creative work. She is associated with Robin Hood Army, which is an NGO works for providing free meals to the needy.

Gouri Gupta leads CSFs work in the area of Education Technology. She works with a portfolio of EdTech products that take high-quality, contextual solutions to young children from low-income backgrounds to support learning. She works with leading researchers to build evidence on what works in EdTech and supports the building of public goods like EdTech Tulna that fill critical white spaces in the EdTech ecosystem. Gouri is part of many global and Indian expert groups in EdTech and skill development.

Prior to CSF, Gouri was part of the founding team at the National Skill Development Corporation, a public-private partnership created by the Govt. of India to invest in skill development ventures in India. Gouri crossed over into the development sector from The Boston Consulting Group where she was a Project Leader working primarily in the financial services domain. Gouri is a Chartered Accountant by training and a management graduate from IIM Bangalore.

Harish Doraiswamy is the Director of the Edtech team at CSF and his work involves working with state governments on their Edtech strategy and implementation. Prior to joining CSF in early 2020, Harish was Vice-President at Pearson India where he was responsible for the K12 School Management, Vocational Education, and International Qualifications verticals. Harish is an alumnus of IIT Madras and IIM Calcutta and has over 30 years of experience across various sectors and functions. He is excited to work on realizing the potential of technology to transform school education for the disadvantaged. In his free time, he loves to enjoy good food, music, the company of his friends, and travel.

Harnoor works as a Project Manager with the District Project Management Unit (UP) team and is based out of Ghaziabad. She holds a Bachelors in Commerce degree from University of Delhi. Prior to CSF, Harnoor worked as a Teach For India Fellow where she ignited the academic journey of about 200 students, infusing passion for learning and fostering tangible growth. Founder of the Harnoor Madhar Foundation, she champions underserved communities in Punjab, ensuring access to quality education and holistic support. In her free time, she likes spending time with animals.

Harshit works as a Project Manager in the Policy & Communications team and is based out of Delhi. Prior to joining CSF, Harshit worked as a Reputation Manager at The Mavericks Communications LLP where he serviced some of Indias leading developmental sector institutions, helping them craft their communications and policy advocacy strategies. He has also worked with the Aam Aadmi Party, heading their survey and political research departments during the Delhi assembly elections and also handled their media department during the Punjab assembly elections.

Harshita works as a Project Lead in the State Reform team and is based out of Bhopal. She has an MBA degree from Nanyang Technological University (NTU), Singapore. She also has 6 years of experience in the education space as a Teach for India Fellow, and with a non-profit startup, Saarthi Education, where she developed and scaled EdTech solutions. She enjoys reading, going on long trails, bicycling and sipping coffee. She is passionate about learning about climate change and sustainability.

Hemani works with the ECE team and is based out of Delhi. She is a science graduate from Miranda House, Delhi University and a qualified teacher. Prior to working with CSF, she has worked at LEAD for more than four years where she designed curriculum, and created books and digital plans with resources for pre-primary.
